Program: Start the Week
Title: 06/12/2010
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00wdf42
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 6 Dec 2010
Andrew Marr talks to the choreographer Matthew Bourne about his vision for Cinderella, while the dance critic, Jennifer Homans sounds the death knell for ballet in her history of the art form. David Aaronovitch also asks whether Freud has had his heyday, in his examination of the continuing significance of the father of psycho-analysis, while the psychotherapist, Jane Haynes, celebrates the enduring appeal and relevance of Proust. Producer: Katy Hickman. Show less